These robust, big (slightly over an inch long) beetles have been flying into windows when we turn on lights in the morning. We've never seen them before at our location. They look similar to the ten-lined June beetle, Polyphylla decemlineata, but markings, shape, and the time of year is wrong. Time of year seems right for Pleocoma behrensi, which is maybe expanding range north a bit?
identificationRemarks: This is not Pleocoma behrensi , which is in the bay area , California . Cheers !
